s you upload your picture in less than a minute. If you prefer, you can stop by the CCC in A-26 and upload it there.<\/li>\n<li>When you register for the ACT it is extremely important to select the colleges you want to see your scores, as ACT scores will no longer appear on your transcript, so therefore Northwest can no longer send them to colleges for you.<\/li>\n<li>If you don&#8217;t choose the colleges you want to receive your scores, you will pay $13 for each score report to be sent to colleges. <em>That will get expensive quickly.<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">College Visits<\/h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\nIf you have not visited colleges that you are interested in, now is the time to do that. Visiting campus allow you get a \u201cfeel\u201d for the environment of the college. For many students, the campus visit is the deciding factor on whether or not they attend that college. When scheduling the visit, make sure to give the college two weeks notice that your requests can be made. You can choose to tour the campus, see the residence halls, meet with a professor, speak with financial aid, etc. You can make it how you want it.<\/p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Career Fits<\/h1>\n<h3>Struggling to figure out your career fit? Check out these websites for personality &amp; career assessments.<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Holland Code Assessment. The Holland Code theory explains work-related behavior such as, which career choices are likely to lead to job success and satisfaction. It also explains other human actions, like success and satisfaction in school and training programs.<br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/personality-testing.info\/tests\/RIASEC.php\">http:\/\/personality-testing.info\/tests\/RIASEC.php<\/a><\/li>\n<li>The O-NET interest profiler can help you figure out your interests are and how they relate to the world of work. You can find out what you like to do utilizing this profiler.<br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.mynextmove.org\/\">www.mynextmove.org<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h1>\nExtra Information<\/h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Complete an activity chart or resume to showcase yourself. The CCC fusion has templates you can utilize.<\/li>\n<li>Follow the CCC \u00a0<strong>@nw_ccc<\/strong> on Twitter for all of the latest information. Also stop by to see Danea Cramer in A-26<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Scholarship Information Upcoming Scholarships Deadlines: November 1 \u2013 KSU and KU November 15 \u2013 FHSU To find additional scholarship opportunities consider creating an account at any of the following sites, each\u00a0provide FREE scholarship searches for you! www.cappex.com www.studentscholarships.org www.zinch.com Scholarships can also be found on the CCC fusionpage. You must apply for admission and be&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"ngg_post_thumbnail":0,"footnotes":""},"categories":[459,4],"tags":[103,93],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2402"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2402"}],"version-history":[{"count":6,"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2402\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2408,"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2402\/revisions\/2408"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2402"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.northwestexplorer.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2402"},{"taxonomy":"po